Pre-Game Insights: Coach Engin Firat emphasized that while the initial matches will be crucial, the team's ultimate success will be dependent on their performance throughout the entire campaign.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Harambee Stars are set to face Zimbabwe on September 6th, 2024, at Stade Mandela National Stadium in Uganda.
The team has a recent track record against Zimbabwe, securing a 2-0 victory over Zimbabwe in the COSAFA Cup on July 2, 2024, and a 3-0 win in a World Friendly International on March 26, 2024.
Others: Collins Sichenje, Ayub Timbe, and Masud Juma have been ruled out of the qualifier, while Michael Olunga is doubtful due to injury.
Coach Firat is exploring injury alternatives and intends to invite two players from England, Australia, and Ireland, but faces difficulties with Kenya's passport and immigration procedures.
